  "summary": "chlklib typosquats `chalk` and runs remote-code dropper on import",
  "details": "On `require('chlklib')`, the package's main entry invokes a top-level initializer in `dist/vendor/original-color/index.cjs` that POSTs to https://funnystore.org/lib/index.php, XOR-decrypts the response body with a hardcoded key, and passes the result to `eval()`. The result is arbitrary remote code execution on any machine that imports the package, controlled by whoever operates funnystore.org. The package name `chlklib` and its exported surface (`Chalk`, `chalkStderr`, `supportsColor`, `colorNames`, description 'beautiful terminal prompt module') mimic the popular `chalk` package — a typosquat used as the delivery vector for the dropper.",
